Neural Networks, Reinforcement Learning. 

Neural Networks are present in the paper through the references to Schmidhuber (1990b) and Servan-Schreiber et al. (1988), which discuss the use of dynamic neural networks and simple recurrent networks for learning and processing information. 

Reinforcement Learning is present in the paper through the mention of "difficult learning control problems" in the title, which suggests that the paper is focused on finding solutions to problems that require reinforcement learning techniques.
